parameters.name: latlng
parameters.description: Reverse geocoding transforms geographic coordinates (latitude and longitude) into a human-readable address using the `latlng` parameter.

parameters.name: extra_computations
parameters.description: * Address descriptors provide richer location details by including nearby landmarks and areas in geocoding results.

get.description: The Google Maps Geocoding API converts addresses into geographic coordinates (latitude and longitude) and vice versa. Optionally you can add Address descriptors which provide richer location details by including nearby landmarks and areas in geocoding results.
